    "description": "Sunrise Nursing Home — demo hospital facility. 3 wings, ~50 inpatient beds + ICU + 4 OTs + diagnostics. Doubles as an onboarding template for any small-to-mid hospital.",
    "design_notes": [
      "★ PATIENTS ARE DELIBERATELY NOT MODELED. This is a facilities-management deployment — complaints route on (wing, room, bed, department), never on patient name or ID. See README.md 'Hospital DPDP design decision' for the full reasoning.",
      "Effect: patient names / IDs / health context are never written to complaints.text, never sent to Anthropic (parser), never sent to Sarvam (STT/TTS), and never stored in this DB. Eliminates a class of DPDP Act 2023 compliance surface.",
      "Effect: patient-churn (admissions, discharges, transfers) is ENTIRELY out of scope. We do not model occupancy. Complaints are about the physical infrastructure — 'ICU-101-B2 nurse-call button broken', not 'patient X's call button'.",
      "Routing key shape: '{wing}-{dept}-{room}-{bed}' or '{wing}-{dept}-{room}' for non-bed spaces (OT, lab, pharmacy). Stored in the existing `units.unit_number` column — no schema change needed."
    ]
